    "summary": "A dust explosion and flash fires occurred at the US Ink facility when combustible dust accumulated in a newly installed dust collection system. The incident began with spontaneous ignition of accumulated sludge-like material in ductwork above mixing tank T-306, leading to a dust explosion in the collector that activated suppression systems. This caused flame propagation back through the ductwork, resulting in flash fires that injured seven workers who had congregated at the pre-mix room entrance.",
